HEADWORD: Hematoma
<hw>Hem`a*to"ma</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧`m⟦adot⟧*t⟦omac⟧"m⟦adot⟧
<it>or</it> h⟦ecr⟧m`⟦adot⟧*t⟦omac⟧"m⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Hema-</er>, and <er>-oma</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A localised leakage of blood from the blood
vessels into nearby tissues, usually confined within a tissue or organ;
especially, a local swelling produced by an effusion of blood beneath
the skin, which may clot and discolor the affected area.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hematophilia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
